args:
Yachiyo is the winner of the duel. However, the
Mukuroshu necromancer shows up to explain
that Saiga's goal was to be reunited with his
dead wife, and how he was so upset by the
murder of Yachiyo's grandfather that he left the
group. He then summons corpses and attacks.
So you showed your ugly mug at last.
Anything you want to say, bub?
As I told you, there is little meaning\nin our exchanging words.
In that case, I'm going to consider our past\nover and you officially dead to me.
Let's go, Saiga. You and me,\nmano a mano!
You think you can beat me with that\nbean-shooter instead of a blade? Ha!
If you are not taking me seriously now,\nyou will soon wish you had...bean.
Save your act for the funny pages!
You...you charged me as though you hold\nno fear of my weapon at all.
*pant* *pant* If I'd given ground, that\nheater of yours would have set me to\ndance. Straight on was the only option.
Shame for you, 'cause if you'd been using\na blade, I'd probably be done for.
I cannot resort to any such petty excuses.\nYou have grown strong, Yachiyo,\nand today you are the victor.
Now do with me as you will.
Per the deal, you gotta do one thing I say,\nno matter what.
Oh, how careless one victory can make\na person. Did your teacher not tell you to\nalways be ready for battle at any time?
Cram it with walnuts, pal!\nYou don't know squat about nothin'!
Ah, but I do—and I must say, I'm sad the\ntwo of you left me out of your little chat.
Still, your attacking each other does\nsave me quite a bit of trouble.
But to think a master assassin famed\neven among the Mukuroshu would be\ndefeated by a little girl like you...
You never had the skill to be reunited with\nyour dead wife, and it was folly to think so.
He hasn't told you? Ah, if only he'd been\nhonest from the start, perhaps this whole\nduel could have been avoided.
All the good, dirty work Saiga did as a\nmember of Mukuroshu was so he might\nbe reunited with his beloved.
Your grandfather was killed for this man's\nchildish self-indulgent dream of reuniting\nwith the dead!
Saiga, is THAT why you're so hot to get\nyour mitts on the Underworld Key?!\nSo you can see my sister again?!
When I found him wracked with despair\nover her loss, I told him something I\nthought might lift his spirits:

In the event we open the gate to the
Realm of the Dead with an Underworld
Key, it would be possible to bring forth
the spirits of the dead.
So you used my dead sister to trick him\ninto your organization? That's lower than\na snake's belly in a wheel rut!
＂Low＂ is such an ugly word. I merely spoke\non a variety of topics in order to awaken\nSaiga from his reverie of grief.
It was Saiga himself who chose to\ndescend down the path to depravity.
All is as this man says: I allied with the\nMukuroshu of my own volition, and can\nmake no excuse for it.
I was deluded—obsessed with the idea of\nseeing my wife—and of my own volition\ndid I abandon righteousness.
Oh, I wouldn't go so far as all that.
In fact, your reason for abandoning the\nMukuroshu was your regret at having killed\nyour own teacher, was it not?
And your reason for coming here and\nhiding your past from this woman is the\nsame: You are ashamed of your deeds.
Everything about you is a miserable mire\nof half-measures, and it is absurd!
Alas, it seems that injured body of yours\nis not ready to obey its mind.
With you in that state, I don't need to go\nout of my way to handle you.
Silent bones, mouldering beneath the\nearth, walk this land once more!\n...Now, my corpses, devour the living.
Where's your head at, bub?! If you slack\nagainst this many corpses, they're gonna\nturn you into hash!
I will clear a path so you might\nflee this place.
Oh no! I ain't gonna let you\ntake the fall for me!
You are Momoyo's dear sister.\nI cannot permit you to die here.
And I ain't gonna let YOU take\nthe big sleep today neither!
You saved me from a surprise attack,\nand I ain't the kind of dame what\ndoesn't pay back what she owes!

I do what's right, and right now, that
means crushin' the Mukuroshu—so let's
bash this cat's teeth in and then kick him
in the guts 'cause he mumbles too much!
How can I refuse so impressive an offer?\nVery well—let us fight to the utmost to\nensure we both escape with our lives.
Now THERE'S the Saiga I remember!\nLet's get this shindig started!
